NBA=E2=80=99s Ratings Slump, Donatella Succession, Sotheby=E2=80=99s
Layoff Saga
--------------------------------------------------------

Happy Friday and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon
assortment of Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni weighs in on the latest Hollywood streaming dr=
ama: Amazon=E2=80=99s controversial decision to send Dwayne Johnson=E2=80=
=99s Red One to Prime Video less than a month after its theatrical debut. T=
he move raises one of the most pressing questions that will define this nex=
t hybrid distribution era: Can Amazon
leverage movie theaters more than theaters can leverage Amazon?

Plus, below the fold: Lauren Sherman explores the fate of Versace after the=
 failed Tapestry-Capri merger. John Ourand takes a microscope to the NBA=E2=
=80=99s dismal early-season viewership. And Tara Palmeri discusses Trump=E2=
=80=99s unusual perspective on political capital with his former White Hous=
